Follow [docs/design/02-gameplay-ux.md](docs/design/02-gameplay-ux.md) §16–17 and [docs/art/visual-vfx.md](docs/art/visual-vfx.md).

**Always visible (Khan 1 minimum):** lives/gate, Gold, Sacred Fire, wave, pause, speed, hero portrait/HP/energy/skill, pad tap → build/manage radial, selected-tower context.

**Contextual (progressive disclosure):** cleanse, brazier, Morale/Farr expansion, Forge, repair/sell, objectives, boss phase — not everything on first battle.

**Alert priority (high → low):** gate danger → tower hijack → regional collapse → boss telegraph → objective → wave update → reward.

**Layout (1920×1080 landscape, thumb zones):**

- Top left: lives, gold, Sacred Fire, wave
- Top right: pause, speed, settings/cleanse when relevant
- Bottom left: virtual stick + hero chip (anchor to `MapCameraUtils.playable_screen_rect`)
- Bottom right: Attack / Heavy / Dodge / Skill cluster + Naft + spell bar
- Pad tap: build radial (empty) or manage radial (occupied) + range ring

Touch targets ~44×44 dp minimum; icons over long labels during waves. No baked text in image UI assets. Wire **touch** via InputMap/actions, not mouse-only. No full-screen panels during active waves unless paused.

Pardeh Break: illustrated “page turn” feel — Fate choice + brief summary, not a heavy meta spreadsheet.
